Ownes-Illinois Holdings Corp filedwith the Securities and Exchange Commission for debt offeringswith principal amounts totalling 2.05 billion dlrs.    The company, which is the successor to Ownens-Illinois Inc,said it plans to offer 250 mln dlrs of senior subordinatednotes due 1996, 500 mln dlrs of subordinated debentures due1999 and 1.3 billion dlrs of junior subordinated discountdebentures due 2003.    Proceeds from the offering, together with about 50 mln dlrsin bank borrowings, will be used to repay or redeem financingincurred in connection with the takeover, it said.    Owens-Illinois, which was taken over by a group led byKohlberg Kravis Roberts and Co, said financing incurred in thetakeover includes a 550 mln dlr bridge loan provided by a bankgroup, 200 mln dlrs provided by two common stock partnershipsand 600 mln dlrs of junior subordinated notes due Sept 17, 1988which were sold to an affiliated of Morgan Stanley and Co Inc.    Other proceeds will be used to pay underwriting costs, thecompany said. Morgan Stanley is the underwriter, it said. Reuter&#3;